{
  "texts": [
    "We found that GPT-4 struggled to consistently provide proper citations and substantiation for the claims made in the generated paper.",
    "Only 40.5% of the sentences that should have been substantiated were adequately supported, while a significant proportion (59.5%) remained unsubstantiated.",
    "The lack of citations, references to non-existent articles, and failure to provide supporting information from cited sources contributed to this issue.",
    "However, it was encouraging to find that a significant number (i.e., 73.8%) of the unsubstantiated claims were verified to be factually accurate through independent sources; it is important to note that the verification process relied on external resources and logical inference.",
    "While GPT-4 demonstrated some ability to generate factual information, the need for external validation, and our inability to substantiate some of the claims, indicated room for improvement."
  ]
}